HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 121
BY REPRESENTATIVE MUSCARELLO
COMMENDATIONS: Commends the Italian Festival Royal Court on the occasion of the
2026 Italian Festival
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend the Italian Festival Royal Court on the occasion of the 2026 Italian Festival.
3 WHEREAS, the Italian Festival is a unique event held each April in Tickfaw,
4 Louisiana, that has become a beloved tradition for both locals and visitors alike; and
5 WHEREAS, the original festival was organized in 1973 and was known as "The
6 Little Italy Festival"; the village of Tickfaw began hosting the Italian Festival in 2009; and
7 WHEREAS, citizens of Italian descent make up a significant portion of south
8 Louisiana's population, and their communities have had a tremendous impact on Louisiana
9 culture, from architectural masonry and foodways to jazz and brass band music; and
10 WHEREAS, the annual Italian Festival in Tickfaw is a family-friendly celebration
11 of Italian-American culture and heritage featuring carnival rides, entertainment from local
12 bands, a parade, a ball, and a pageant; there is a spaghetti cook-off where judges select
13 winners in the categories of gravy, meatballs, and table decorations; and
14 WHEREAS, Lily DiBenedetto, a young woman of many gifts and talents, reigns as
15 the 2026 Italian Festival Queen; Kim Notariano reigns as the Spaghetti Queen; Veda Abene
16 reigns as Grand Marshal; and Carlos Notariano reigns as King; and
17 WHEREAS, the 2026 Italian Festival royal court also includes Teen Queen, Kailyn
18 DeMarco; Junior Queen, Bayley Thompson; Deb Queen, Mila Fonseca; Little Queen, Joanna
19 Oliphant; Petite Queen, Amelia Prima; Tiny Queen, Raelyn Wright; Toddler Queen,
20 Lakelynn Wright; and Princess, Victoria Bender; Robert Fugarino serves as the chairperson
21 for this year's festival; and
